race.comment: CALL ME SASSY (3) slow into stride on debut before launching late with an eye-catching third over 1000m at this track. Comes out of a decent rating race and has the upside to win this at her second race start. BOLD AND BLAZEN (2) strengthened up over the break and gets a better set-up today. Worked hard early from the awkward gate when he gripped on late to secure second over this track and trip. Tongue-tie goes on and stalks the good tempo. EMERY (1) showed potential in her first two campaigns. Total forgive first up from the outside gate when a battling eighth over this track and trip. Claim helps and she can turn her form around quickly. NOBLE RUBY (8) just under a month between runs second-up when a fading seventh over 1000m at Queanbeyan. Up in class and has a key jockey change from the low draw. Worthy contender.
